OL,3,CGrenfell survivors go to Ground Zero
OL,4,Cto learn from America's darkest day
OL,6,FSurvivors and bereaved families of the
OL,7,FGrenfell disaster have travelled to
OL,8,FGround Zero to see for themselves how
OL,9,FNew York remembers the September 11th
OL,10,Fterror attacks.
OL,12,FNo permanent memorial has yet been
OL,13,Fagreed in West London where Grenfell
OL,14,FTower still stands. In America, a
OL,15,Ftribute of remembrance honors the many
OL,16,Fpeople who died.
OL,18,FThe twin reflecting pools, each nearly
OL,19,Fan acre in size, are surrounded by the
OL,20,Fnames of those who lost their lives on
OL,21,FAmerica's darkest day.
